<!-- Async WordPress.com Remote Login -->
<script id="wpcom_remote_login_js">
var wpcom_remote_login_extra_auth = '';
function wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( element_id ) {
	var dom_node = document.getElementById( element_id );
	if ( dom_node ) { dom_node.remove(); }
}
function wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_classes( class_name ) {
	var dom_nodes = document.querySelectorAll( '.' + class_name );
	for ( var i = 0; i < dom_nodes.length; i++ ) {
		dom_nodes[i].remove();
	}
}
function wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup() {
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_classes( "wpcom_remote_login_msg" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_key" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_validate" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_js" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_request_access_iframe" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_request_access_styles" );
}

// Watch for messages back from the remote login
window.addEventListener( "message", function( e ) {
	if ( e.origin === "https://r-login.wordpress.com" ) {
		var data = {};
		try {
			data = JSON.parse( e.data );
		} catch( e ) {
			wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup();
			return;
		}

		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN' ) {
			// Clean up the login check iframe
			wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_key" );

			var id_regex = new RegExp( /^[0-9]+$/ );
			var token_regex = new RegExp( /^.*|.*|.*$/ );
			if (
				token_regex.test( data.token )
				&& id_regex.test( data.wpcomid )
			) {
				// We have everything we need to ask for a login
				var script = document.createElement( "script" );
				script.setAttribute( "id", "wpcom_remote_login_validate" );
				script.src = '/remote-login.php?wpcom_remote_login=validate'
					+ '&wpcomid=' + data.wpcomid
					+ '&token=' + encodeURIComponent( data.token )
					+ '&host=' + window.location.protocol
						+ '//' + window.location.hostname;
				document.body.appendChild( script );
			}

			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP, not logged in, so redirect
		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN-REDIRECT' ) {
			window.location = 'https://wordpress.com/log-in?redirect_to=' + window.location.href;
			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP, storage access failed, remove the request
		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN-REMOVE' ) {
			var css_zap = 'html { -webkit-transition: margin-top 1s; transition: margin-top 1s; } /* 9001 */ html { margin-top: 0 !important; } * html body { margin-top: 0 !important; } @media screen and ( max-width: 782px ) { html { margin-top: 0 !important; } * html body { margin-top: 0 !important; } }';
			var style_zap = document.createElement( 'style' );
			style_zap.type = 'text/css';
			style_zap.appendChild( document.createTextNode( css_zap ) );
			document.body.appendChild( style_zap );

			var e = document.getElementById( 'wpcom_request_access_iframe' );
			e.parentNode.removeChild( e );

			document.cookie = 'wordpress_com_login_access=denied; path=/; max-age=31536000';

			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP
		if ( data.msg === 'REQUEST_ACCESS' ) {
			console.log( 'request access: safari' );

			// Check ITP iframe enable/disable knob
			if ( wpcom_remote_login_extra_auth !== 'safari_itp_iframe' ) {
				return;
			}

			// If we are in a "private window" there is no ITP.
			var private_window = false;
			try {
				var opendb = window.openDatabase( null, null, null, null );
			} catch( e ) {
				private_window = true;
			}

			if ( private_window ) {
				console.log( 'private window' );
				return;
			}

			var iframe = document.createElement( 'iframe' );
			iframe.id = 'wpcom_request_access_iframe';
			iframe.setAttribute( 'scrolling', 'no' );
			iframe.setAttribute( 'sandbox', 'allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation' );
			iframe.src = 'https://r-login.wordpress.com/remote-login.php?wpcom_remote_login=request_access&origin=' + encodeURIComponent( data.origin ) + '&wpcomid=' + encodeURIComponent( data.wpcomid );

			var css = 'html { -webkit-transition: margin-top 1s; transition: margin-top 1s; } /* 9001 */ html { margin-top: 46px !important; } * html body { margin-top: 46px !important; } @media screen and ( max-width: 660px ) { html { margin-top: 71px !important; } * html body { margin-top: 71px !important; } #wpcom_request_access_iframe { display: block; height: 71px !important; } } #wpcom_request_access_iframe { border: 0px; height: 46px; position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; min-width: 100%; z-index: 99999; background: #23282d; } ';

			var style = document.createElement( 'style' );
			style.type = 'text/css';
			style.id = 'wpcom_request_access_styles';
			style.appendChild( document.createTextNode( css ) );
			document.body.appendChild( style );

			document.body.appendChild( iframe );
		}

		if ( data.msg === 'DONE' ) {
			wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup();
		}
	}
}, false );

// Inject the remote login iframe after the page has had a chance to load
// more critical resources
window.addEventListener( "DOMContentLoaded", function( e ) {
	var iframe = document.createElement( "iframe" );
	iframe.style.display = "none";
	iframe.setAttribute( "scrolling", "no" );
	iframe.setAttribute( "id", "wpcom_remote_login_key" );
	iframe.src = "https://r-login.wordpress.com/remote-login.php"
		+ "?wpcom_remote_login=key"
		+ "&origin=aHR0cHM6Ly9ibGFja2xpc3RkZWNsYXNzaWZpZWQubmV0"
		+ "&wpcomid=9473618"
		+ "&time=1603821769";
	document.body.appendChild( iframe );
}, false );
</script>

		function addLoadEvent(func) {
			var oldonload = window.onload;
			if (typeof window.onload != 'function') {
				window.onload = func;
			} else {
				window.onload = function () {
					oldonload();
					func();
				}
			}
		}

<h2>üî¥ Script: 4:1 Esteban (‚Ññ 79)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 9/22/2016 in the US<br />
Permalink: <a href="http://wp.me/pDKwi-3ip" rel="nofollow">http://wp.me/pDKwi-3ip</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2d4Z8sp" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2d4Z8sp</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director: </b>Michael <b>Watkins</b><br />
<b>Written by: </b>Jon <b>Bokenkamp</b>, John <b>Eisendrath</b><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 4:1 Esteban (‚Ññ 79)</h3>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Blurb: </b>Alexander Kirk (aka Constantin Rostov) is holding Liz (aka Masha Rostova) captive in Cuba. Baby Agnes is missing. Red must find them before Kirk leaves the island with them.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red, Dembe and Kate are in the villa where Liz, Agnes and Tom were taken. Red is distressed, conjuring up dark images of what happened with each splash of blood, shard of glass or abandoned toy he sees. Ominous music plays ‚Ä¶ ]</p>
<blockquote><p>
‚ô™ pulsing my senses weak ‚ô™
</p></blockquote>
<p>[ Tom is bound in the trunk of a late &#8217;50s blue Dodge sedan ]  </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Ominous music continues ‚Ä¶ ]<br />
[ Red, Dembe and Kate (&#8220;Mr Kaplan&#8221;) are investigating the site where Liz, Tom and Baby Agnes were taken ]<br />
Kate: [ Referring to splash of blood on wall ] Critical hit. He couldn&#8217;t have gone far.<br />
Dembe: He wouldn&#8217;t go to a hospital. </p>
<blockquote><p>
‚ô™ now time has run its course ‚ô™<br />
‚ô™ there is no other way ‚ô™
</p></blockquote>
<p>Mr Kaplan (Kate): The bleeder works for Kirk. He&#8217;ll know where to find them.<br />
Dembe: I have a location.<br />
Kate: I was trying to help. He has to know that.<br />
Dembe: I&#8217;m not on your side here, Kate. </p>
<blockquote><p>
‚ô™ pulsing my senses weak ‚ô™<br />
‚ô™ I was hunting, I went running ‚ô™<br />
‚ô™ now time has run its course ‚ô™<br />
‚ô™ there is no other way ‚ô™ </p>
<p>Tunefind: <a href="http://bit.ly/2cBUkd2" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2cBUkd2</a>
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Silenced gunshot (üí•) ] [ Silenced gunshot (üí•) ] [ Grunts ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> I need to speak with the patient.<br />
Doctor: He&#8217;s gone.<br />
<b>Red:</b> As you well know, one of the keys to my success is a clear and consistent understanding of my own limitations. So often people overestimate themselves, misapply their gifts. The cleaner suddenly fancies herself the strategist. Wisdom is learning the boundaries of one&#8217;s designated lane. For instance, this, I will do poorly. Clumsily, with more mess than necessary. It&#8217;ll take longer and be considerably more unpleasant to boot. [ To Kate ] But I can&#8217;t very well have you do it, can I?<br />
[ Red proceeds to cut the head off the dead man ] [ Flesh cutting and squishing ] [ Click and thud ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Manny Soto: Raymond Reddington, my favorite rubio. Ay carajo, I haven&#8217;t seen you since you snuck off at Carnival.<br />
[ Red takes severed head from bag ]<br />
Manny Soto: Red, Jesus. What&#8217;s wrong with you?<br />
<b>Red:</b> We&#8217;re looking for a name. Take a close look, Manny. He worked for a man who abducted someone I care about.<br />
Manny Soto: He&#8217;s a cop.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Who&#8217;s his rabbi?<br />
Manny Soto: I don&#8217;t know, but I know who might. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Aram: Is it true? She&#8217;s alive?<br />
Samar: Apparently.<br />
Aram: Wait, wait. Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait. How is that&#8230; there were complications during labor. And the doctor, he declared her dead.<br />
Samar: He lied.<br />
Aram: But there was a funeral. I-I was a pallbearer.<br />
Samar: Yes, and who knows what was in that casket? It was a charade, Aram.<br />
Aram: So Agent Keen is alive? Uh, but her funeral and her death&#8230; She faked her death.<br />
Why would she do that?<br />
Ressler: To get away from Reddington. So that her and Tom and Agnes could have a normal life.<br />
Aram: Away from us?<br />
Samar: Yes, after everything we did for her.<br />
Ressler: Best we could tell, Liz and Tom&#8217;s plan was to go into hiding in Cuba. Alexander Kirk found them.<br />
Aram: Why? What does he want with Agent Keen?<br />
Ressler: Look, all we know right now is that when Reddington got there, Liz and Tom were gone.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
Cooper: I just got off the phone with the embassy in Havana. Briefed them on Kirk, gave them the tail number to his plane. If that was how he was planning to get off the island, that&#8217;s not gonna happen.<br />
Aram: And, uh, what about Agnes?<br />
Ressler: At this point, we don&#8217;t know.<br />
Cooper: Notify FBI headquarters. Elizabeth Keen is alive. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Balzan: The plane is ready.<br />
Alexander Kirk (aka Constantin Rostov): Mato and the baby?<br />
Balzan: Not yet.<br />
Kirk: Notify me as soon as they&#8217;re here.<br />
Liz Keen: My baby.<br />
Kirk: She&#8217;s on her way.<br />
Liz: That&#8217;s what you said before.<br />
Kirk: Masha‚Äì<br />
Liz: My name is Elizabeth.<br />
Kirk: I understand that you have questions, that you&#8217;re upset.<br />
[ Liz punches Kirk in the face, bloodies his nose ] [ Grunts ] [ Guard cocks his gun ]<br />
Kirk: I&#8217;m sorry it has to be like this.<br />
Liz: You&#8217;re not my father.<br />
Kirk: Well, I am, Masha. I am. And I intend to prove that to you. Agnes will be brought here, but the person doing that has a job to do first.<br />
Liz: What job? With Tom? What are you doing to Tom? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Salsa music on the radio ] [ Engine rumbling ] [ Agnes wailing ] [ Tom is banging in the trunk ]<br />
Tom: Let me out!<br />
[ Tom punches out a tail light and waves his fingers out the ragged opening. A young girl notices Tom&#8217;s fingers and alerts her father. Her father calls the police ]<br />
[ Agnes continues wailing ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red approaches a table of cops playing poker ] [ Laughter ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> There&#8217;s nothing more depressing than a failed Communist state. It doesn&#8217;t even really pay to be corrupt. When dirty cops play poker in America, they&#8217;re able to play for real money.<br />
Cop: [ Spanish w English subtitles ] What&#8217;s up, Manny? Who is this guy?<br />
Manny Soto: He&#8217;s a friend. He&#8217;s just looking for a name.<br />
[ Red tosses a thick wad of bills on the table ] [ Red removes the severed head from the bag and sets it on the table by an empty chair ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Let&#8217;s raise the stakes. A new game. You tell me who the head worked for, you keep the money, a 5-way split.<br />

Tom: To get you to trace the signal, Aram.<br />
Aram: Oh. Oh, you already&#8230; uh&#8230; Wow, that&#8217;s, uh, that is impressive. [ Beep, typing on keyboard ] Okay. Hang on. I&#8217;m on it.<br />
Tom: Thank you.<br />
Aram: Did you know? At the christening, when you made me a godfather to Agnes‚Äì<br />
Tom: Look, man, I know you&#8217;re upset, all right? But right now is not the time.<br />
Aram: I&#8217;m trying to ping the signal. Waiting for a reply&#8230; from both of you.<br />
Tom: Aram&#8230; of course I knew.<br />
Aram: I&#8217;ll let you know when, uh, I find the signal.<br />
Tom: Thank you. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz is running through a wooded area. Agnes is crying ]<br />
Liz: Shh, shh, shh. Shh. Shh. [ Crying continues ] Please, Agnes, stop crying. Mommy&#8217;s here. Shh, shh, shh. [ Agnes continues crying ]<br />
[ Romina appears wielding a knife and swipes at Liz ]<br />
Liz: Think about what you&#8217;re doing. What are you gonna do? Hurt me? Hurt my baby? Kirk will kill you if you do. Are you a mother? Do you have children? Look at her&#8230;<br />
[ Blade whooshes, Romina goes down ] [ Liz throws the baby blanket aside ‚Äì she has a piece of firewood and is about to attack Romina with it ]<br />
[ Mato appears and points the gun at Agnes, who is lying on the ground ]<br />
Mato: Hey! [ Gun clicks ]<br />
Liz: No! [ She holds her hands up. Agnes resumes crying ]<br />
Mato: Little mama, you got spirit. Get up. [ To Romina ] Get the baby.<br />
[ The float boat circles in for a water landing ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Kirk: You&#8217;ll learn to trust me. Get the baby and the things. We&#8217;re leaving.<br />
Liz: Like hell we are. No!<br />
Kirk: I wish there was another way, I do, but Reddington&#8217;s on his way.<br />
Liz: Agnes!<br />
Kirk: [ To his men ] Come on. Get her onboard.<br />
[ They muscle Liz into the float plane, leaving Agnes behind with Romina ] </p>

<b>Red:</b> A small fishing port in Playa Larga. We&#8217;re on our way.<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script: 4:2 Mato (‚Ññ 66)</h2>

Program air date: 9/29/2016 in the US<br />

<h3>‚≠ï Script 4:2 Mato (‚Ññ 66)</h3>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Blurb: </b> Liz has been separated from her infant daughter Agnes, forced by Alexander Kirk (aka Constantin Rostov), a man claiming to be her father, to leave Cuba headed &#8220;home.&#8221; Red and Mr Kaplan rescue Agnes, only to have her taken again by the mysterious shamanic Mato.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Kirk, who claims to be Liz&#8217;s father Constantin Rostov, has forced Liz to accompany him on a float plane to a place he tells her is &#8220;home.&#8221; ]<br />
Kirk: He won&#8217;t find you‚Äì Reddington‚Äì if that&#8217;s what you&#8217;re hoping for or worried about.<br />
Liz: Tom&#8217;s alive. You don&#8217;t have Agnes. I&#8217;m not worried about anything.<br />
Kirk: I won&#8217;t apologize for trying to restore my family.<br />
Liz: Even if it means destroying mine.<br />
Kirk: Reddington‚Äì He took you from me.<br />
Liz: And you hate him for it, for stealing your child. I know how that feels.<br />
Kirk: You would&#8217;ve been with Agnes now if you hadn&#8217;t tried to escape.<br />
Liz: Yes. But then again, so would you.<br />
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]<br />
Kirk: Tell me.<br />
Mato: I got the girl.<br />
Kirk&#8217;s Find a way across the Straits, then contact my office in the Keys. Do it quickly. Agnes has been away from her mother too long. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Suddenly, Liz lunges at the pilot. The plane nosedives ] [ Gunshot üí• ]<br />
Pilot: She&#8217;s gonna kill us! Aah!<br />
[ Wind whistling ] [ Grunts ] [ Gunshot üí• ‚Äì The pilot is fatally shot. Liz leans over the pilot to grab the controls of the plane tries to level it. The plane is about to hit the water ‚Ä¶  ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ The car with Dembe, Red, Mr Kaplan (&#8220;Kate&#8221;) and baby Agnes was rammed by Mato, who has taken Agnes. Tom drives up in a red pickup truck ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> The child&#8230;<br />
[ Truck stops ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> No.<br />
[ Grunts, groans ] [ Groans ] [ Sighs ]<br />
Tom: Liz and Agnes.<br />
<b>Red:</b> No. Please assist Mr. Kaplan.<br />
Tom: You all right?<br />
[ Red clears throat ] [ Dembe grunts ]<br />
Tom: Where are they?<br />
<b>Red:</b> In danger. How did you find us?<br />
Tom: I had Aram tracking that car. I spent the better part of the day stuck in the trunk.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Who was the driver?<br />
Tom: Had to be one of Kirk&#8217;s hired hands. 6-foot, rough trade, dark skin. Likes Western wear.<br />
Kate: Mato. I saw his face.<br />
Tom: Who&#8217;s Mato?<br />
Kate: A finder. A tracker. Killer when necessary.<br />
Tom: How do we find him?<br />
Kate: I don&#8217;t know.<br />
<b>Red:</b> You don&#8217;t know or you won&#8217;t say?<br />
Kate: We had a mutual friend. He gave Mato his start as a skip tracer. It was years ago.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Little Nikos.<br />
Kate: I can talk to him. If he knows anything, he&#8217;ll tell me.<br />
<b>Red:</b> West Texas&#8217; favorite bail bondsman. An Amarillo institution for 25 years to life. Dembe, call Edward. Tell him to ready the jet. We&#8217;re gonna pay a visit to Little Nikos. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz wakes in the crashed plane. Kirk is unconscious ] [ Water lapping ] [ Gasps ] [ Grunts ] [ Metal creaking ] [ Object thuds, water pouring ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Aram runs up metal stairs still the Post Office ]<br />
Aram: Excuse me. Sorry. It&#8217;s Mr. Reddington.<br />
<b>Red:</b> [ On phone ] We have two targets‚Äì Elizabeth Keen and Agnes Keen‚Äì traveling separate paths to an unknown location. Constantin Rostov, also know as Alexander Kirk, fled with Elizabeth in a private seaplane that departed from Playa Larga&#8230; mm, less than an hour ago, due west.<br />
Aram: What about Agnes?<br />
<b>Red:</b> I have a lead on Agnes. She was abducted by one of Kirk&#8217;s private contractors, a high-priced tracker known only as Mato. He missed the flight off the island.<br />
Samar: Then he&#8217;s trapped in Cuba. There&#8217;s no way he&#8217;ll make it past the PNR after the international incident you just caused there.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Ordinarily I would agree with you, Agent Navabi, but Mato isn&#8217;t your garden-variety mercenary. From what I&#8217;m told, he&#8217;s an Indian‚Äì part Sioux, part I don&#8217;t know what, son of a Shaman. Mato could sneak up on a deer in a glade and smack it on the rump. He&#8217;ll find his way off the island.<br />
Cooper: We&#8217;ll notify the seaports just in case. Good luck. And let us know what you turn up. [ Receiver beeps ] Contact Customs and Border Patrol. They work with the Coast Guard to monitor the air and waters around Cuba.<br />
Samar: Sir, I don&#8217;t understand why we&#8217;re going to such extremes‚Äì<br />
Cooper: Agent Ressler is on a return flight from Cuba. It&#8217;s time to set aside your personal feelings and help out this investigation. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Kate: This is my fault. If anything happens to Elizabeth or the baby&#8230;<br />
Tom: You have nothing to apologize for. You tried to help us find a normal life. I&#8217;d take that risk again. [ To Red ] I don&#8217;t regret trying to get away from you.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Of course you don&#8217;t. Regret requires age or wisdom.<br />
Tom: We were trying to protect Agnes.<br />
<b>Red:</b> I guess that didn&#8217;t work out. When we get to Amarillo, I think it would be best to do as I say, both of you. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Liz: Mayday, mayday, mayday. Plane down off the coast of Havana. 23 degrees, 52 minutes north.<br />
[ Water pouring ]<br />
Liz: 82 degrees, 49 minutes south. Mayday, mayday, mayday. Can anyone hear me?<br />
Kirk: My sat phone.<br />
Liz: Gone.<br />
[ Static crackling ]<br />
Kirk: You need to untie me, Masha.<br />
Liz: Mayday, mayday, mayday, is anyone there?<br />
[ Loud clank ]<br />
Kirk: What was that? You need to know that Agnes is safe. She&#8217;ll be cared for.<br />
[ Metal creaking ]<br />
Kirk: You see anything?<br />
Liz: One of the pontoons is taking on water. We don&#8217;t have long.<br />
Kirk: Untie me! Masha, I&#8217;m your father. You can&#8217;t let me drown.<br />
Liz: Watch me.<br />
[ Static ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Captain Daly: We&#8217;ve got every sonar operator in the Miami district working on this. We launched the search as soon as I received your call.<br />
Samar: Any chance the plane is still in range?<br />
Daly: A light aircraft, flying low and slow? We&#8217;ll find it. We monitor 2 million square miles of ocean from Miami.<br />
Samar: Agent Ressler, welcome back. This is Captain Daly. He&#8217;s our liaison with the US Coast Guard.<br />
Daly: I&#8217;m authorized to give you full access to our radar screens.<br />
Ressler:  If that seaplane is flying low, won&#8217;t it avoid detection?<br />
Daly: Most radar transmitters are on the ground, aimed at the sky. Ours float in the sky on balloons, looking down. They&#8217;re designed to detect small aircraft, like the one you described. If you don&#8217;t mind me asking, who&#8217;s on the plane?<br />
Ressler: Friend.<br />
Samar: [ At the same time as Ressler ] A fugitive.<br />
Daly: Sounds complicated. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red and Kate get out of the car ]<br />
Kate: When we get inside, let me talk to him. He and I have history.<br />
<b>Red:</b> He and I don&#8217;t. I&#8217;ll be more persuasive.<br />
Kate: Is that what this has come to? The chance for you to punish me by hurting someone I care about?<br />
<b>Red:</b> You are not my concern. Agnes is. If someone you care about is hurt in the process of finding her, so be it.<br />
Kate: Do you remember what I looked like that night? Lying in the street, my head torn open&#8230; Annie&#8217;s body in front of me.<br />
<b>Red:</b> You know I don&#8217;t know what you looked like. I was away.<br />
Kate: Right, but he does. Little Nikos sat by my bed in the hospital. When I healed, he gave me work, a reason to push on. He&#8217;s a decent man. I&#8217;m only here to serve you today because of his kindness.<br />
<b>Red:</b> You may speak to him first. Briefly.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Door bell jingles ]<br />
Maisie: Afternoon. Can I help you?<br />
[ Door closes ]<br />
Kate: Little Nikos, please.<br />
Maisie: Oh, wish I could oblige, Miss&#8230;<br />
Kate: Mr. Kaplan, an old friend.<br />
Maisie: Mr. Kaplan, I wish I could oblige, but Nikos is takin&#8217; a little nap.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Perhaps it&#8217;s time for a wake-up call.<br />
Maisie: Uh, I&#8217;m afraid that&#8217;s not possible. He&#8217;s in surgery.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Where?<br />
Maisie: His stomach.<br />
<b>Red:</b> And where might we find his stomach? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red and Kate burst into an operating room where a laparoscopic surgery is underway ]<br />
Ellen: I told him he couldn&#8217;t come in.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Oh, my. Me and my timing.<br />
Surgeon: What the hell is going on?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Is this a lap band? I knew all those desserts would catch up with Little Nikos one day. I think I see some baklava in there.<br />
Surgeon: Put that down. Helen, get him out of here. Call building security.<br />
<b>Red:</b> I need your capable team here to wake up your patient.<br />
Surgeon: What? Call security right now.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Wake him up.<br />
Surgeon: I can&#8217;t. We&#8217;re in the middle of a procedure. I&#8217;d be putting his life in danger.<br />
<b>Red:</b> His life&#8217;s already in danger. [ Draws gun ] How &#8217;bout yours?<br />
[ Monitor beeping steadily ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Kirk: There are no life vests, no inflatable rafts. We&#8217;re gonna flip. Our only chance is out there, holding onto the pontoons.<br />
Liz: You mean my only chance. [ Unzips pocket ] You&#8217;re not going anywhere. [ Seat belt clicks ] [ Exhales sharply ] [ Gunshot (flare) üí• ]<br />
Kirk: We&#8217;re not gonna survive unless we trust each other.<br />
Liz: I&#8217;ll never trust you.<br />
[ Kirk has gotten the gun when Liz was distracted with the flare. He points it at her ]<br />
Kirk: We&#8217;re a family. Not Reddington. Us. If you wanna hold your child in your arms again, we need to trust each other.<br />
[ Kirk hands the gun to Liz ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Ressler: The Coast Guard just picked up a brief ELT signal from a light aircraft west of Havana, somewhere in the Gulf of Mexico.<br />
Cooper: An ELT signal? Are you telling me their plane went down?<br />
Samar: It appears that way, sir.<br />
Cooper: But we have a location for them.<br />
Ressler: It&#8217;s not that simple. This ELT signal&#8217;s an older model. Analog frequency.<br />
Aram: No digital signal to carry GPS coordinates.<br />
Samar: ELTs are notoriously unreliable, especially if they&#8217;re&#8230; submerged underwater.<br />
Captain Daly: We&#8217;ve narrowed the search field to 220 square miles. SAR teams are gearing up now.<br />
Aram: I know this is not about me, it is about Agent Keen, but I don&#8217;t know if I have the strength to lose her again.<br />
Samar: None of us do.<br />
Cooper: Stay on it. Say a prayer. And notify me the minute you have an update.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Surgeon: He&#8217;s awake and in excruciating pain. I gave him a self-administering morphine drip to manage his discomfort. Even that won&#8217;t be enough unless you get what you want quickly and leave.<br />
<b>Red:</b> [ To Kate ] Remember&#8230; we&#8217;re getting what we need, one way or another.<br />
[ Monitor beeping steadily ] [ Nikos groans softly ]<br />
Little Nikos: Kate. What are you&#8230; What&#8217;s happening?<br />
Kate: We only have a minute. Raymond Reddington is here. [ Nikos grunts ] He wants Mato.<br />
[ Breathing heavily ] [ Groans ] [ Click ] [ Groans ]<br />

It&#8217;s been a death sentence for generations of men in his family, except a distant uncle, who had contracted the Ribowski virus. After getting the virus, the uncle lived longer than any other Rostov with the blood disease.<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script: 4:4 Gaia (‚Ññ 81)</h2>

<h3>‚≠ïScript 4:4 Gaia (‚Ññ 81)</h3>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Blurb: </b>Liz has learned from Katarina&#8217;s journal that her mother had been &#8220;assigned&#8221; to Red by the KGB but had fallen in love with him. She also learned that the reason Kirk has searched for her is that he needs her to save him from a deadly form of hereditary anemia passed only from father to son. Now Agnes may provide him with what he needs.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS) [ Owen Ayers aka &#8216;Gaia&#8217; is watering plants at his make-shift homestead deep in the forest. The place consists of two old school buses and some makeshift outbuildings. He goes into a bus and uses a forceps to pull a bloody wad out of his nose. Makes a call ]<br />
(RADIO BEEPS)<br />
Owen Ayers aka &#8216;Gaia&#8217;: [ On phone ] Look, Maya&#8230; you need to listen. I have a new target. You need to leave, both of you. You need to pack the car and get away&#8230; as far away from here as possible. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Going-away party ] (APPLAUSE)<br />
Warren: All right, easy there, easy there. Seriously! Throttle back! Or I might get the impression you&#8217;re really gonna miss me. (LAUGHTER) You know, I&#8217;ve been flying choppers for 40 years from Air America to Hudson Sky Tours, and I got to admit&#8230; I hated every minute of it. (LAUGHTER) Listening to Marty defending his pathetic Cubs&#8230;<br />
Marty: Cubbies! (LAUGHTER)<br />
Warren: The only reason I ever put up with the guy was because he&#8217;s the best damn mechanic in the business. (APPLAUSE)<br />
Yeah, yeah.<br />
[ Gaia drops a pill into a drink, gives it to Marty ]<br />
Gaia: [ To Marty, low voice ] Grew up in Wrigleyville.<br />
Warren: Truthfully, I could say the same about every one of you, so it&#8217;s been a pleasure working with you, and if you ever get to Palm Desert, please, promise me you won&#8217;t call!<br />
(LAUGHTER)<br />
Warren: Cheers!<br />
All: Cheers. Cheers. Cheers.<br />
(APPLAUSE)<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Marty is in bathroom, looking into the mirror ] (DOOR OPENS, CLOSES) [ Gaia enters ]<br />
Marty: Wrigleyville. How you know Warren?<br />
Gaia: Charter service. Shuttling the 1%. I&#8217;m a mechanic, too.<br />
Marty: Can&#8217;t fly without us.<br />
(COUGHING) (GRUNTS) (BREATHES SHARPLY) (BREATHING RAPIDLY)<br />
Gaia: Hold on. Won&#8217;t be long.<br />
(STRAINED BREATHING)<br />
(SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE)</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz opens her laptop ]<br />
(COMPUTER RINGING)<br />
Kirk/Rostov: [ On Liz&#8217;s computer screen ] Hello, Masha. I know it&#8217;s late, but I wanted to speak to you alone.<br />
Liz: Where is she?<br />
Kirk: I never wanted you to be apart from her.<br />
Liz: Where&#8217;s my daughter?!<br />
Kirk: Right here, safe.<br />
Baby Agnes: (COOING) (CRYING)<br />
Liz: (SNIFFLES, SIGHS) If you so much as&#8230; If you hurt her&#8230; I know the truth. The only reason you came for me&#8230; the only reason you want Agnes is because what&#8217;s killing you, it&#8217;s a genetic disease, and you think we can cure you, that our blood can&#8230;<br />
Kirk: Yes, the blood is what I need, but it&#8217;s not what I want. What I want is for us to be together, but that can&#8217;t happen until Reddington&#8217;s out of your life. Only you can make that happen. I see you&#8217;re wearing your mother&#8217;s bracelet. I&#8217;m glad. I want you to know that your baby is safe. This link is open day or night any time you want to see Agnes.<br />
(COOING)<br />
Liz: Hi, baby. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Tom: What do you mean, you don&#8217;t want to trace the link?<br />
Liz: You don&#8217;t think he&#8217;s thought of that? The second he discovers we traced it, he&#8217;ll take it away, take her away.<br />
Tom: Liz, the only way we&#8217;re gonna get her is by finding where that link is coming from.<br />
Liz: I don&#8217;t think he&#8217;ll hurt her.<br />
Tom: Of course he will. She&#8217;s his last chance of survival.<br />
Liz: If he hurts her, he loses me.<br />
Tom: Yeah, and lives.<br />
Liz: What does Kirk want more than anything in the world? For me to trust him&#8230; to care for him. And because it&#8217;s what he desires most, it&#8217;s the easiest way to deceive him. He&#8217;ll see what he wants to see&#8230; my affection. He won&#8217;t see what&#8217;s real&#8230; my deception. This link is an opportunity for me to get close to Kirk. And I can&#8217;t do anything to jeopardize that.<br />
Tom: Liz, I think you&#8217;re being naive.<br />
Liz: I know you think that. And I&#8217;m asking you to trust me. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red and Liz are sitting at a table outside under sun umbrellas next to a river ]<br />
Liz: Dembe said you had a lead on Agnes.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Some years ago, I had a rather awkward encounter with a bull shark while diving off the Great Barrier Reef. I actually think it was trying to be affectionate, even a little forward. (LAUGHS) But the net result was excruciating. But I did spend a glorious month submitting to the healing hands of an utterly divine lighthouse keeper on Bramble Cay&#8230; a low-lying island that&#8217;s rapidly being submerged by rise in the sea levels due to climate change.<br />
Liz: Climate change?<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Our next blacklister is devoted to protecting the Earth from the greatest threat to its existence as we know it&#8230; us. He&#8217;s a stealth eco-terrorist known only as Gaia&#8230; Earth Mother in Greek mythology.<br />
Liz: Okay, so, the connection between this Earth Mother and Agnes is what?<br />
 <b>Red:</b> What is not relevant. Only where. We must find this man&#8230; unless you have a better lead on Kirk. Has he reached out to you?<br />
Liz: No, he hasn&#8217;t.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Gaia then.<br />
Liz: A stealth eco-terrorist? Isn&#8217;t that an oxymoron?<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Nine times out of 10, the public reacts to an act of eco-terror by getting angry at the terrorist rather than the environmental offense he seeks to draw attention to. By disguising his sabotage in accidents, Gaia succeeds in focusing the public&#8217;s rage on the actual danger, not the criminal who exposes it. Shall I go on? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz debriefs the task force ]<br />
Liz: 2011, 10,000 gallons of MCHM, a toxic chemical used to wash coal, was leaked from the Fullerton Chemical Plant. Now, this spill made it into the drinking water in the local towns. A few hundred people were poisoned, including two children and three elderly victims who later died. Environmentalists had warned of the danger of a spill for years, but no one listened until this leak, and then the EPA finally mandated changes.<br />
Aram: So it worked. In Gaia&#8217;s mind, he protected people.<br />
Ressler: Yeah, well, tell that to the parents who lost their kids.<br />
Cooper: So, he kills innocent people to make a point that innocent people are in danger.<br />
Samar: How does taking down this lunatic get us closer to Kirk and Agnes?<br />
Liz: Reddington won&#8217;t say.<br />
Ressler: Even though this is allegedly about finding your daughter. Prick.<br />
Cooper: I want this guy found. Go over every detail of that spill. If it was sabotage, Gaia left a trail. Find it. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Aram: Hey. So, about last night&#8230; Sorry we couldn&#8217;t talk. But if you want to grab lunch today and chat&#8230;<br />
Samar: It&#8217;s okay. I figured it out.<br />
Aram: Figured what out?<br />
Samar: Whether or not to submit my transfer request. I decided I should, so I did.<br />
Aram: So it&#8217;s official? Uh&#8230; I mean, I-I knew you were thinking about it, but you actually&#8230;<br />
Samar:  It&#8217;s not a big deal. It&#8217;s for the best.<br />
Aram: Right, sure. That is, you&#8230; you&#8217;ve given it a lot of thought, so&#8230; &#8230;congratulations.<br />
Samar: I shouldn&#8217;t keep Ressler waiting. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ On site at the Fullerton Chemical Plant, going through evidence from the chemical spill ]<br />
Ressler: This is crazy. An entire team of Chemical Safety Board investigators looked into this after the spill. Nothing was flagged.<br />
Samar: This is box 7. There are 43 more evidence boxes. (SIGHS)<br />
Ressler: Googled Aram&#8217;s new girlfriend.<br />
Samar: Why?<br />
Ressler: Why do guys do anything? To see if she was hot, which she is.<br />
[ Man pushes in cart with additional boxes of evidence ]<br />
Ressler: I thought we had everything.<br />
Man: Everything from CSB. These are from the internal investigation. I told you folks you&#8217;re wasting your time. That spill was an accident. Two days before the leak, a veteran DEP inspector looked over the storage tanks. He didn&#8217;t see anything wrong, and neither did the other guy about two weeks earlier.<br />
Ressler: What other guy? I just looked at the list of scheduled inspections, and there was only one in the month prior.<br />
Man: Scheduled, yeah, but we get spot inspections from time to time.<br />
Ressler: We&#8217;re gonna need to see everything you have on that spot inspector&#8230; now. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ At a gas station coffee self-service table ]<br />
Gaia: Borron Energy Services. That&#8217;s fracking, right?<br />
Field Inspector: Well, I&#8217;m a field inspector.<br />
Gaia: That&#8217;s bad stuff, man&#8230; fracking. Messing up the water table. There&#8217;s places where you can light a fire with what&#8217;s coming out of the tap. You&#8217;re making people sick.<br />
Field Inspector: You want to know what&#8217;s in your sweetener? The chemicals in that creamer?<br />
[ Gaia drops a pill in the Field Inspector&#8217;s coffee ]<br />
Field Inspector: [ Continues ] What about the plastic bottles in that watering cooler? Look around. Everything&#8217;s killing us. So spare me the guilt trip&#8230; and the righteous lecture. I earn my living&#8230; same as you.<br />
(DOOR OPENS, BELL DINGS) (DOOR CLOSES) (BELL DINGS)<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Gaia follows the Field Inspector out to his truck ]<br />
(CHOKING) (BREATHING HEAVILY)<br />
Gaia: You were right&#8230; The world is just filled with things that are gonna kill us.<br />
[ Gaia takes the Field Inspector&#8217;s helmet and his laptop ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Kate is lying on a bed in a dark, rough room, a ragged bandage on her right cheek. The right side of her face is matted with blood ]<br />
(DOOR OPENS) (DOOR CLOSES) (SNAPPING FINGERS)<br />
[ A grizzled old man ‚Äì the Hunter ‚Äì enters with his dog ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Aram: Okay, ladies and gentlemen, I think we have a suspect. Okay, check this out. The Kentucky chemical plant wasn&#8217;t the only facility that received a visit from a spot inspector. Three of the other accident sites also received spot inspections within a few weeks of their failing.<br />
Liz: So that&#8217;s this guy&#8217;s M.O. He&#8217;s not breaking into these facilities. He&#8217;s walking through the front door.<br />
Samar: You said you had a suspect.<br />
Aram: Right. I got surveillance video from three of the facilities on this particular spot inspector.<br />
(COMPUTER BEEPING)<br />
[ Photos of Gaia come up from each of the three sites ]<br />
Liz: That&#8217;s our guy.<br />
Cooper: Alert the DHS and circulate the photo. Put a name to that face.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
Ressler: Hey. You okay?<br />
Samar: Yeah, I&#8217;m fine.<br />
Ressler: Because Aram told me you put in for a transfer. Navabi, trust me, I understand how angry you are with Keen for doing what she did&#8230;<br />
Samar: Yes, and that is part of why I&#8217;m leaving, but it&#8217;s not just that. It&#8230; It&#8217;s this place. You never know where you stand with anyone&#8230; whether they&#8217;ll be there for you when you need them.<br />
Ressler: If there&#8217;s anything I can do to get you to reconsider, you let me know. I&#8217;ll do it. You&#8217;re a good partner.<br />
Samar: I wish there was. I really do. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Kirk: Six months?<br />
Dr. Reifler: Maybe. Maybe less. But we both knew this day was coming. Your body would start rejecting the transfusions. It&#8217;s remarkable it&#8217;s lasted this long.<br />
Odette: There is a solution.<br />
Kirk: We&#8217;ve already discussed this.<br />
Dr. Reifler: It&#8217;s unacceptable.<br />
Odette: Easy for you to say. You&#8217;re not the one that&#8217;s gonna die.<br />
Kirk: No, I am, and I agree with Sebastian.<br />
Odette: The girl is your only option.<br />
Kirk: We&#8217;re exploring other cures.<br />
Odette: We were&#8230; before we lost the Ribowski virus, before the U.S. government froze your assets.<br />
Dr. Reifler: If the girl is a genetic match&#8230; and there&#8217;s no guarantee that she is&#8230; extracting stem cells from such a young child is extremely dangerous and could prove fatal.<br />
Odette: Hippocrates bounds the doc to do no harm. He&#8217;s giving you coulds, mights. I am under no such obligation. I am giving you facts. We are out of time, and we are out of resources. The only way to save your life [ she touches his hand ] is if we put that child&#8217;s in jeopardy. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Liz: I think we&#8217;ve got something. We put out a general alert to all government and private facilities&#8230; oil and gas, chemical plants.<br />
Ressler: And?<br />
Liz: A gas pipeline inspector in Newark was found dead in his car this morning. Heart attack.<br />
Samar: Could be a coincidence.<br />
Liz: Maybe, but he had an appointment to evaluate a gas pipeline in Westchester County.<br />
Aram: He&#8217;s there.<br />
Cooper: Was there a positive I.D.?<br />
Aram: No, but&#8230;<br />
Samar: So it&#8217;s a supposition.<br />
Aram: Uh, no, actually. According to security at the facility, a guy showed up less than an hour ago claiming to be filling in for the usual inspector.<br />
Cooper: Ressler, Navabi, get there. Keen, call the plant manager and the county sheriff. See if they can evacuate the area without tipping off Gaia that we&#8217;re on our way. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Samar: Agents Navabi and Ressler. Where is he?<br />
Plant Security: Sector 7. Said he had to check the pressure gauges.<br />
(ENGINE REVVING, TIRES SCREECHING) (GUN COCKS) (GUN COCKS)<br />
[ Gaia takes off running ]<br />
Ressler: Stop! Federal agent!<br />
Samar: He&#8217;s got a gun! Ressler!<br />
(ENGINE STARTS) (ENGINE REVS, TIRES SCREECH)<br />
[ Gaia jumps in his truck, guns it. Ressler and Samar follow in pursuit. Ahead are two police cruisers. Gaia slams on his brakes and tries to reverse, but Ressler&#8217;s car blocks the way  ]<br />
(TIRES SCREECHING) (SIRENS WAILING) (TIRES SCREECH) (TIRES SCREECHING)<br />
Officer: Get out of the vehicle!<br />
(OFFICER SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY) (ENGINE REVS)<br />
[ Gaia hits the gas, smashes through the police cars and is gone ]<br />
(SIGHS)<br />
Ressler: Damn it. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ At a laundromat ] (DOOR OPENS, BELL DINGS) (BELL DINGS)<br />
Krantz: Long time, Martell&#8230; or whatever you&#8217;re calling yourself now.<br />
Tom: Martell will be fine. You?<br />
Krantz: There&#8217;s a bunch to choose from. England, France, Malta&#8230; your basic NATO alliance.<br />
Tom: Malta&#8217;s not in NATO.<br />
Krantz: (CHUCKLES) Always were a stickler.<br />
Tom: Why don&#8217;t we just stick with Krantz?<br />
Krantz: So, what&#8217;s on your mind, Martell?<br />
Tom: I got a job for you and your crew&#8230; digital trace&#8230; break-in.<br />
Krantz: I&#8217;m all ears. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Aram: The pipeline targeted by Gaia carries fracked gas&#8230; a process that environmentalists oppose.<br />
Samar: Why? Because fracking creates jobs and energy independence?<br />
Aram: Maybe. Or maybe because of this. San Bruno, 2010. A ruptured natural-gas pipeline caused a 72-foot-long crater and killed 8 people. Last year in Allentown, another one exploded underneath a city street, killing five.<br />
Cooper: So it fits the M.O. He was gonna cause an accident to provoke public outrage.<br />
Liz: Yeah, but how? We didn&#8217;t find any explosives. What was he doing?<br />
Aram: Research. Look at where Gaia&#8217;s tools and fake I.D. badge were found&#8230; the spot of the highest gas pressure. I think he was trying to identify the most vulnerable point, the perfect place to hit.<br />
Samar: If it&#8217;s that dangerous, then why hasn&#8217;t it already been shut down?<br />
Aram: Because there are safety rules in place for new pipelines, but they don&#8217;t always apply for existing lines.<br />
Cooper: Which is probably the point he&#8217;s trying to make.<br />
Aram: It gets worse, actually. I had an expert over at PHMSA do a blast-radius projection just to see what kind of damage an explosion at this spot would cause. In an urban area like this, we&#8217;re talking hundreds of homes, schools, a city hospital&#8230; and this&#8230; Stone Park, the largest nuclear power plant on the eastern seaboard of the United States.<br />
Cooper: Where are we on the fake I.D. badge you recovered?<br />
Liz: Nowhere. But Reddington says he&#8217;s got a guy who might be able to help.<br />
Cooper: Reddington&#8217;s guy. Who is he? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Bowling alley ] (PINS CLATTER) (CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Forgive the intrusion, keglers.<br />
Glen: Aw. What do you want?<br />
 <b>Red:</b> I have a job for you, Glen.<br />
Glen: News flash&#8230; I&#8217;m off the clock, Reddington.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> It&#8217;s a matter of some urgency.<br />
Glen: No, it&#8217;s a matter of some me time, boundaries, work-life balance, the pause that refreshes.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> We need to know who made this I.D.<br />
Dembe: [ To Glen ] Your release point is off.<br />
Glen: Yeah, but I&#8217;m a charming conversationalist, so the ladies don&#8217;t mind.<br />
Dembe: Keep your elbows in.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Some haste would be appreciated. A child&#8217;s life is in the balance.<br />
Glen: Hologram. RFID chip. Ji Ming&#8217;s your man. Chinese expat. Loves all things Americano. Last time we had dinner, he ordered bull fries. Ugh. You ever had bull&#8230;<br />
Glen: [ On phone ] Ji Ming? Jellybean here. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
(Glen and Ji Ming are SPEAKING MANDARIN)<br />
 <b>Red:</b> All I need is an address, Glen.<br />
(SPEAKING MANDARIN) (SPEAKING MANDARIN)<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Glen, an address.<br />
Glen: Hey, I don&#8217;t see you jumping in here, pal. I&#8217;m doing the best I can. A night course in Mandarin doesn&#8217;t get you much past reading the menu and &#8220;Hey, honey, your caboose looks tasty in those slacks.&#8221;<br />
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)<br />
 <b>Red:</b> What the hell is he saying?<br />
Glen: Honestly, he says he doesn&#8217;t like you. He says you look like his third wife and that&#8230;<br />
 <b>Red:</b> What?<br />
Glen: Right. That you have no appreciation for the fact that bowling is like s*x. It&#8217;s about rhythm and flow. You can&#8217;t just stop in the middle and go back to pick up the spare you missed because some jerk shouted out during the middle of your roll.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> He&#8217;s already given you the address, hasn&#8217;t he?<br />
Glen: Yeah, but it&#8217;s a little off the grid. (CLEARS THROAT) I&#8217;d ditch the wingtips.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Dembe, call Elizabeth. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red and Liz are at Gaia&#8217;s place. They enter Gaia&#8217;s living quarters ]]<br />
 <b>Red:</b> What do you see?<br />
Liz: Um&#8230; he&#8217;s withdrawn, a loner, and yet he&#8217;s committed to making the world a cleaner place. Photo of a pregnant woman. But no child. Maybe the child was taken or&#8230; or died.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> We&#8217;re going to get her back, Lizzy.<br />
Liz: Tidal charts for the Hudson.<br />
 <b>Red:</b> Stone Park is on the Hudson. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Gaia barges into his ex-wife Maya&#8217;s home. A child (age 2 or 3) is sitting in a stroller, facing away ]<br />
Maya: If you don&#8217;t leave, I&#8217;m gonna call the police!<br />
Gaia: The only reason I&#8217;m here is because you didn&#8217;t return my calls. It&#8217;s not safe.<br />
Maya: You&#8217;re violating the restraining order.<br />
Gaia: I&#8217;m the least of your problems! You have to leave. And going to your mother&#8217;s isn&#8217;t far enough.<br />
Maya: What are you planning?<br />
Gaia: You need to leave the state.<br />
[ Gaia goes to his son, Skyler. The right side of Skyler&#8217;s face and head are horribly disfigured ]<br />
Gaia: Hey, Sky. How&#8217;s my little man? You&#8217;re going on a car trip with Mommy. Someplace pretty with trees turning all kinds of colors. Won&#8217;t that be nice? [ To Maya: ] You need to get on the road now. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Inside the Hunter&#8217;s rustic cabin ] (Kate GROANING) (FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)<br />
Hunter: Hey, there.<br />
(CHAIR THUDS) (Kate GASPS)<br />
Hunter: [ Kindly ] Hmm. What happened out there, young lady? You&#8217;re not dressed for the woods. Can you talk? That&#8217;s all right. You don&#8217;t need to say nothing. We&#8217;re gonna get you fed. Build your strength up. Plenty of time to talk later. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz is watching Agnes on the video feed ]<br />
(COOING) (DIALING)<br />
Tom: [ On phone ] Hey.<br />
Liz: I&#8217;m looking at our little girl. It&#8217;s almost like a baby monitor, like she&#8217;s in the next room.<br />
Tom: Only she&#8217;s not. Kirk has her.<br />
Liz: I know. I asked you this morning to trust me, not to trace the link. I want you to know it means everything to me that you are okay with that. Thank you.<br />
Tom: Everything&#8217;s gonna be all right, Liz. Blow her a kiss for me.<br />
Liz: Okay. I love you.<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script 4:6 The Thrushes (‚Ññ 53)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 10/27/2016 in the US<br />

&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
<b>Director:</b> Terrence <b>O&#8217;Hara</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Daniel <b>Knauf,</b> Dave <b>Metzger</b><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 4:6 The Thrushes (‚Ññ 53)</h3>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Blurb: </b>Red has a plan to draw out Alexander Kirk (aka Constantin Rostov), who Red and Liz have discovered has hacked into the task force&#8217;s computers. Red suspects a group named the Thrushes performed the difficult technical feat. Liz remains torn between Kirk and Red. Liz and Tom&#8217;s baby, Agnes, becomes a pawn in game of charades in which no one but Liz knows her true intentions.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Minsk, Belarus ]<br />
Ren√© Le Bron: The President of the United States is not God, gentlemen. His judgment is not final. He has judged you to be human rights violators, drug traffickers, impediments to democracy, and he has signed Executive Order 13405, freezing 760 million Euros of your money. My judgment is that you are sanctioned businessmen with no cash to run your business. So&#8230; 600 million Euros, secured on a tarmac a plane less than 14 kilometers from this room. Your money, gentlemen. To do with as you please. Infrastructure, weapons, medicine, sex, drugs, rock and roll&#8230; It matters not to me. All I ask in return is a market rate on the loan until your assets are unfrozen. At which point, you will transfer them to me.<br />
Man: You offer 600 million and expect 760 million when sanctions are lifted?<br />
Le Bron: Yes. 160 million&#8230; plus interest. For substituting my judgment for the president&#8217;s. You can keep the plane. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Elevator bell dings ] [ Muzak plays ] [ Elevator bell dings ] [ Laughter ] [ Speaking native language ] [ Elevator door closes ] [ The group that just boarded quickly put down Le Bron&#8217;s group, leaving only Le Bron standing ]<br />
Le Bron: I have three-quarters of a billion in cash parked at MSQ. If you let me go now, it&#8217;s yours.<br />
Oscar: Do you, now? My team seized that money 30 seconds after you cut the feed to the conference room. Can we keep the plane?<br />
[ Oscar&#8217;s men put a white sack over Le Bron&#8217;s head and lead him off the elevator ]<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Red in his Mercedes ]<br />
[ Cellphone beeps ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Hello, Oscar. I trust you secured the package.<br />
Oscar: And his cargo. Shall I deduct the balance of my fee from the cash at hand?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Yes. And direct a generous contribution in Le Bron&#8217;s name to the Belarusian Refugee Fund.<br />
Oscar: All of it?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Don&#8217;t be absurd. Oh, and, Oscar, that plane is mine. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red briefs the task force ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Iranian mullahs, Mexican cartels, radical despots&#8230; Your government declares them enemies and freezes their assets to influence their behavior. Economic sanctions are relatively easy to implement and historically effective. Until now. Agent Navabi, would you be so kind? [ Mouse clicking ] Ren√© Le Bron&#8230; Financier of terrorist states and criminal organizations. When your government freezes their assets, Le Bron offers them sizable loans, rendering the sanctions toothless and affording the bad actors the ability to continue conducting business as usual. When the sanctions are lifted, Le Bron makes a hefty profit by pocketing the frozen assets he insisted his borrowers put up as collateral.<br />
Ressler: Brilliant idea. Sick, but brilliant.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Yes, Donald. Truth be told, I&#8217;m disappointed I didn&#8217;t think of it.<br />
Liz: Why bother when you can have us arrest him and then take his place?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Good point.<br />
Aram: Sorry. Did I miss something? I-Is this about going after Kirk and&#8230;<br />
Liz: Finding my daughter? No, it isn&#8217;t. Apparently, empire building takes precedence.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Alexander Kirk is a client of Le Bron&#8217;s. After your government froze Kirk&#8217;s assets, he turned to Le Bron for a loan.<br />
Liz: You&#8217;re always giving us someone&#8217;s six degrees of separation from Kirk.<br />
<b>Red:</b> I intercepted Le Bron in Minsk closing a deal. He&#8217;s willing to cooperate, but on a condition I am powerless to fulfill&#8230; Immunity from prosecution.<br />
Ressler: So you think that he&#8217;ll cooperate in exchange for witness protection?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Well, one can hardly expect unconditional virtue from creatures like Ren√© Le Bron.<br />
Liz. So I&#8217;ve learned.<br />
Cooper: I&#8217;ll have to clear immunity with Cynthia Panabaker. Ressler, Navabi, Aram, clear the logistics for transfer of custody. Keen, a word.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
Cooper: I can&#8217;t pretend to know the stress you&#8217;re under. But from where I sit, he&#8217;s doing everything in his power to find Agnes.<br />
Liz: And kill Kirk.<br />
Cooper: You have a problem with that?<br />
Liz: Alexander Kirk is my father.<br />
Cooper: You have proof?<br />

<h3>‚≠ï Script 4:7 Dr Adriane Shaw (‚Ññ 98)</h3>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Blurb: </b>At last Liz and Tom have been reunited with baby Agnes. </p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ A man is in an observation room, his face inflamed and his skin erupting in pustules ]<br />

Kirk: Great. [ Door closes ] I&#8217;m going to die, but I feel great. [ Monitor beeping steadily ] What would you do if you had more money than you could ever spend?<br />
Liz: Travel the world with my family&#8230; twice.<br />
Kirk: You could get away from him. Somewhere safe where he couldn&#8217;t find you.<br />
Liz: Sure. But like my dad always said, if wishes were horses, beggars would ride. My adopted dad, Sam Milhoan.<br />
Kirk: My entire life, all I ever wanted was to make you safe, protect you. And in the end, the only way I&#8217;m able to do that is by dying.<br />
Liz: I don&#8217;t understand.<br />
Kirk: It&#8217;s yours. Everything I have. I&#8217;m leaving you my fortune.<br />
Liz: Which you&#8217;ll have plenty of time to spend, because you&#8217;re not dying. Not now, anyway. I told your doctor that I&#8217;ve decided to be your donor. They&#8217;re running the tests now to confirm we&#8217;re a match.<br />
Kirk: Why did you decide to help me?<br />
Liz: Because you didn&#8217;t ask.<br />
[ Door opens ] [ Cooper ushers Odette inside ]<br />
Cooper: Your lawyer&#8217;s here to see you.<br />
Odette: If I could have a moment alone with my client&#8230;<br />
Cooper: Of course. For now.<br />
[ Liz and Cooper leave ]<br />
[ Odette speaking Russian ]<br />
Kirk: Out, but not cured. Only she can do that.<br />
Odette: An FBI agent and a life saver. You must be so proud.<br />
Kirk: She&#8217;s agreed to be my donor. I need a day, maybe two. And I need you to watch your mouth.<br />
Odette: We had everything before her. And now look at us. I am not apologizing for disliking her. [ She kisses him languorously ] The extraction plan is in place. We move on your signal.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
On waiting room TV:</p>
<blockquote><p>
Announcer: We&#8217;re told dozens have been injured in this bus accident. And they&#8217;ve been transferred to the Walter Reed facility for further&#8230; [ Indistinct conversations ]
</p></blockquote>
<p>[ Siren wailing in distance ]<br />
Tom: Excuse me. I&#8217;m here to see Elizabeth Keen.<br />
Desk Attendant: She was on the bus?<br />
Tim: What bus?<br />
Desk Attendant: The accident. Is she a patient?<br />
Tom: No, no, no. She&#8217;s visiting a family member, Alexander Kirk. She said he was in a locked ward.<br />
Desk Attendant: You say her name is Elizabeth Keen?<br />
Tom: That&#8217;s right. She&#8217;s my wife.<br />
Desk Attendant: Sir, your wife is a patient. She was admitted an hour ago.<br />
Tom: Admitted for what? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Waiting room door closes ] [ Sighs ]<br />
Liz: Don&#8217;t say it.<br />
Tom: What is there to say? I gave you my opinion. You ignored it.<br />
Liz: I didn&#8217;t ignore it. I just&#8230; didn&#8217;t agree.<br />
Tom: Okay, what are the risks?<br />
Liz: Risks for me? None.<br />
Tom: None? Are you sure?<br />
Liz: All I have to do is give blood. [ Sighs ] I should&#8217;ve told you sooner. I&#8217;m sorry. Just everything is happening so fast.<br />
Tom: I get it. Fine. Help him if you have to. But promise me you&#8217;re not gonna hurt yourself in the process.<br />
Liz: I promise.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Aram: [ On phone ] Harbor Patrol and Customs will meet you on site.<br />

Aram: Yeah, already e-mailed it to you. 16 crew members and the licensed cargo is medical equipment.<br />
Ressler: How convenient.<br />
Aram: Not just any equipment‚Äì thermal cyclers, centrifuges, incubators. Yeah, these are products used in genome research.<br />
Ressler: Okay, thanks. [ Cellphone beeps ]<br />
Samar: That was the unit I dispatched to get Dr. Rayburn. He left the clinic an hour ago, accompanied by a large black man and a middle-aged white guy. In a hat. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Dr Shaw: [ On phone ] We&#8217;re about to dock. What&#8217;s the emergency?<br />
[ Red is in the Mercedes with Dr Rayburn ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Dr. Shaw! Or should I call you, Dr. Bloom? Either way, I&#8217;ll skip the pleasantries. We haven&#8217;t much time.<br />
Shaw: Who is this?<br />
<b>Red:</b> I&#8217;m here with your colleague, Dr. Rayburn, who can confirm we have a situation. As we speak, the FBI is raiding his medical clinic.<br />
Rayburn: Sonia, he knows everything about the research, The Coroner.<br />
<b>Red:</b> I&#8217;m like the Ghost of Christmas Past&#8230; and Future, which is how I know the FBI will board your ship the moment it docks.<br />
Shaw: Whoever you are, why should I believe you?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Belief is such a relative concept. Is there a God? Are we alone in the universe? What the hell have they found out there in Area 51 anyway? I prefer to think of your decision as judicious risk assessment. I have considerable resources to put at your disposal. I&#8217;m here to help you, Dr. Shaw. If you don&#8217;t want to go to jail, listen to me carefully. Firstly, is there a helipad on your ship? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Wright: We got your results back.<br />
Liz: How&#8217;d I do?<br />
Wright: We couldn&#8217;t harvest enough stem cells to justify a transfusion.<br />
Liz: So what happens now?<br />
Wright: With a compatible donor, we could do a surgical procedure to harvest marrow directly from the cavity of your hip bone.<br />
Tom: No. Surgical procedure carries risks, right? For Liz?<br />
Wright: While it&#8217;s a minor procedure, an infection could cause necrosis of the hip, which could impact mobility. Or a fat embolism that could affect multiple organ systems.<br />
Liz: And if those are risks I&#8217;m willing to take?<br />
Tom: Which you&#8217;re not. We talked about this.<br />
Wright: What risks you are or not willing to take are irrelevant. Even if the dialysis had worked, the hospital won&#8217;t transfuse your stem cells into Mr. Kirk unless and until we receive confirmation that you&#8217;re a genetic match.<br />
Liz: You sent my blood out for testing hours ago.<br />
Wright: And you know about the bus accident. You saw the incoming. The system is overwhelmed.<br />
Liz: And if he dies before the tests come back confirming I&#8217;m a match?<br />
Wright: I understand you feel he has nothing to lose, but that is not how we make hospital policy. Liz: The tests could come back five minutes late. Two. You&#8217;re okay with that?<br />
Wright: Of course not. I made it clear. Your blood work should be the lab&#8217;s top priority. They&#8217;ll get your results as fast as possible. And I&#8217;ll be in touch as soon as they do. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Siren wailing, tires screech ]<br />

Lasko: I don&#8217;t know who that is.<br />

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]<br />

Liz: Do you have the lab results?<br />

Liz: I know I&#8217;m breaking my promise. But I have to do this.<br />

I&#8217;m confident Mr. Kleeb can encourage you to answer some of my questions, Raymond. As I said, I have many. Now, let&#8217;s start at the beginning.<br />
[ Kirk injects Red&#8217;s hand ]</p>

[ Kirk injects Red in the neck ]<br />

<h3>‚≠ï Script 4:9 Lipet&#8217;s Seafood Company (‚Ññ 111)</h3>
<blockquote><p>

<h2>üî¥ Script: 4:10 The Forecaster (‚Ññ 163)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 1/12/2017 in the US<br />
Permalink: <a href="http://wp.me/pDKwi-3YR" rel="nofollow">http://wp.me/pDKwi-3YR</a><br />
